(
 "Congratulations, you've mastered structural editing! Here's your cheat sheet:

Slurp  (Alt+Right):  Expand parens to grab the next item
Barf   (Alt+Left):   Shrink parens to release the last item
Splice (Alt+Up):     Remove the enclosing parens entirely
Cleave (Alt+Down):   Split one group into two at the cursor

These four moves, combined with typing parentheses and deleting, let you reshape any expression while keeping your code balanced at all times. Happy editing!")
